<h2>What Landlords and Lenders Actually Check</h2>

<p>When a landlord reviews your pay stubs, they are looking for internal consistency: does gross pay minus deductions equal net pay? Do the deductions seem reasonable for the income level? Does the employer name match what you said on the application? Do the dates make sense -- are these recent stubs, not from 18 months ago?</p>

<p>What they are NOT doing: verifying exact federal tax bracket calculations or auditing the specific percentages. However, a stub where the numbers clearly do not add up -- gross pay minus deductions does not equal net pay, for example -- is an immediate red flag. The arithmetic accuracy matters even if the specific tax rate applied is not scrutinized in detail.</p>

